<title>POLAND: Polish KPW clear Energomontaz Poludnie for trade.</title>
<headline>Polish KPW clear Energomontaz Poludnie for trade.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-07-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Polish Securities Commission (KPW) has cleared for public trade the initial public offering of builder Energomontaz Poludnie SA, the KPW said in a statement on Thursday.</p>
<p>The firm's 743,000 existing shares have also been approved for trade.</p>
<p> Tranches		  No Of Shares	   Subscription</p>
<p>			     Offered		  Period</p>
<p> Large-investor	  250,000		  August 11-20</p>
<p> Small-investor	  107,000		  August 11-20</p>
<p> Lead Manager:	   BOS brokerage</p>
<p> Price range  (PLN):    30-45/shr</p>
<p> Lead Underwriter:     N.A.</p>
<p> EARNINGS DATA	   1997 forecast	  1996</p>
<p>(in million of PLN)</p>
<p> Net profit:	     4.2		     2.6</p>
<p> Pre-tax:		  6.8		     n.a.</p>
<p> Sales:		    n.a.		    61.4</p>
<p>Main Shareholders:</p>
<p> Rafako			   - 49 pct of shares</p>
<p>Bank Ochrony Srodowiska (BOS)  BBOSs - 11.4 pct of shares  No of existing shares:			743,000</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
